<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,266,1372]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
COMMENTS. The presence of very large double-rimmed septate pores in the submargin is most reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hempel, 1922 b: 1160 -" authorityYear="1161" box="[239,391,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maritimus">
<emphasis box="[239,391,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">A. maritimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but possessing a broad submarginal band of wide-rimmed pores suggests possible closer affinities with other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bondar" authorityYear="1923" box="[578,700,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capiangae">
<emphasis box="[578,700,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">capiangae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[723,807,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[723,807,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, to which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="2008" box="[1101,1298,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicaraguensis">
<emphasis box="[1101,1298,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">A. nicaraguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs.
</paragraph>
